That's good!

62
00:04:09,140 --> 00:04:11,560
Kyou-chan, do you know her?

63
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,140
One of Kirino's friends.

64
00:04:13,810 --> 00:04:17,270
Pleased to meet you. My name is Aragaki Ayase.

65
00:04:17,270 --> 00:04:20,360
Likewise! I'm Tamura Manami.

66
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:23,150
Um... I'm Kyou-chan's childhood friend.

67
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:25,740
Hey, Ayase...

68
00:04:25,740 --> 00:04:26,910
Yes?

69
00:04:28,950 --> 00:04:32,370
She hasn't really been acting differently...

70
00:04:32,370 --> 00:04:34,460
It's the usual Kirino.

71
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:36,330
I see...

72
00:04:36,330 --> 00:04:39,500
If anything were to happen, I would know.

73
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:40,800
I'm her best friend.

74
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:42,420
I guess.

75
00:04:42,970 --> 00:04:45,590
Sorry to ask such a weird question.

76
00:04:45,590 --> 00:04:48,680
Yes. I'll be off, then.

77
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:50,100
Yeah. See you.

78
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:50,760
Good bye.

79
00:04:54,890 --> 00:05:02,610
Well, I did suggest the event, but Miss Kiririn was quite active in the preparations.

80
00:05:02,610 --> 00:05:05,570
I don't think she was forcing herself or anything...

81
00:05:05,570 --> 00:05:08,030
Maybe I'm just overthinking things?

82
00:05:09,370 --> 00:05:13,120
Well, I suppose it's natural for you to be concerned about Miss Kiririn.

83
00:05:13,870 --> 00:05:15,620
I'm not, idiot!

84
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:19,380
Sorry to bother you.

85
00:05:19,380 --> 00:05:20,380
I'm out.

86
00:05:20,380 --> 00:05:21,590
See you.

87
00:05:21,590 --> 00:05:22,920
Nyoro~n.

88
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:31,560
What's up?

89
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:33,720
Can you come to my room?

90
00:05:48,410 --> 00:05:51,580
Your room's a lot cleaner than last time.

91
00:05:51,580 --> 00:05:53,950
I cleaned up a bit.

92
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:58,750
So, what did you want to talk about?

93
00:05:58,750 --> 00:06:02,000
Is it that final life counseling you were talking about?

94
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:05,880
Well, that's one way to put it.

95
00:06:07,380 --> 00:06:09,260
Well, whatever. Let's hear it.

96
00:06:09,260 --> 00:06:10,220
Wha—

97
00:06:10,220 --> 00:06:11,180
Hm?

98
00:06:11,890 --> 00:06:13,390
Nothing.

99
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:16,640
I want you to buy me an eroge.

100
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:18,890
What the hell?!

101
00:06:21,810 --> 00:06:23,150
This one!

102
00:06:23,150 --> 00:06:26,780
"I'd Never Steal Something Like Onii-chan's Pantsu!!"

103
00:06:26,780 --> 00:06:27,900
And this one!

104
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:29,700
3D Custom Imouto!

105
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:31,160
OniPan and CusImo.

106
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:33,080
What kind of abbreviations...

107
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:36,870
I want you to line up for the midnight release and get it for me.

108
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:41,130
This is seriously your last life counseling?

109
00:06:41,130 --> 00:06:41,880
Yeah.

110
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:43,670
Why are you asking me to do this?

111
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:47,670
Because I want to play them as soon as possible, obviously.

112
00:06:47,670 --> 00:06:55,220
My plan is to sleep in the afternoon until you get it, then play until morning, finishing at least one route.

113
00:06:55,220 --> 00:06:58,930
What is with you? You'd go that far?

114
00:06:58,930 --> 00:07:01,440
Of course I would. Naturally.

115
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:04,480
But that store is in Akiba, right?

116
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:08,490
Even if I buy it at midnight, I won't get back until after 1.

117
00:07:08,490 --> 00:07:10,070
If Dad finds out—

118
00:07:10,070 --> 00:07:12,200
I'll take care of that.

119
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:15,410
I'll give you status updates on him by phone.

120
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:20,120
I want to play it as soon as possible!

121
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:22,290
Please? This is the last time...

122
00:07:24,670 --> 00:07:25,790
Please?

123
00:07:30,170 --> 00:07:32,550
Fine! I just need to go buy it, right?

124
00:07:32,550 --> 00:07:35,300
Really? Alright!

125
00:07:36,930 --> 00:07:41,980
Sorry, Akagi. Can you make it look like I'm staying at your place tonight?

126
00:07:41,980 --> 00:07:45,560
Yeah, sure. Go get that Tamura-san, eh?

127
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,190
See you.

128
00:07:48,530 --> 00:07:51,030
Sounds like he's misunderstanding this...

129
00:07:52,990 --> 00:07:54,780
Man, it's cold.

130
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:06,210
Are these all... Kirino's kind?

131
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:13,220
All customers for the midnight release, line up here!

132
00:08:24,810 --> 00:08:26,900
Someone came here on that?

133
00:08:27,270 --> 00:08:30,030
Um... Is this the end of the line?

134
00:08:30,030 --> 00:08:31,570
Oh, yeah.

135
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:35,490
A-Akagi?!

136
00:08:35,490 --> 00:08:37,620
Kousaka?!

137
00:08:40,450 --> 00:08:44,670
I asked you to make it look like I'm staying at your place!

138
00:08:44,670 --> 00:08:46,380
What are you doing buying eroge?!

139
00:08:47,380 --> 00:08:49,500
It's a long story...

140
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:53,510
Wait! I thought you were going somewhere nice with Tamura-san!

141
00:08:53,510 --> 00:08:55,380
What are you doing buying eroge?!

142
00:08:56,340 --> 00:08:58,390
It's a long story...

143
00:09:00,890 --> 00:09:03,810
It looks like we both have extenuating circumstances.

144
00:09:03,810 --> 00:09:07,900
Why don't we say we never met here?

145
00:09:10,860 --> 00:09:15,240
Neither you nor I was at a midnight release in Akihabara.

146
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:16,160
We did not line up.

147
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:19,700
Of course, we did not buy any eroge!

148
00:09:23,950 --> 00:09:26,960
Friends expect nothing in return!

149
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:31,210
Customers with pre-orders for Homoge Club, line up here please!

150
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:32,960
Okay!

151
00:09:37,930 --> 00:09:39,890
Y-Y-You!

152
00:09:39,890 --> 00:09:42,850
Is that what they call a full-on homo game?!

153
00:09:42,850 --> 00:09:44,310
Kousaka?!

154
00:09:44,310 --> 00:09:46,690
You are definitely misunderstanding things!

155
00:09:46,690 --> 00:09:48,850
Listen to me! Look into my eyes!

156
00:09:48,850 --> 00:09:49,860
Stay away from me!

157
00:09:49,860 --> 00:09:51,610
I'm not homo!

158
00:09:51,610 --> 00:09:54,440
Sure, that's a full-on homo game!

159
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:57,740
But my sister asked me to get it!

160
00:09:57,740 --> 00:10:00,740
Your sister is still a middle schooler!

161
00:10:00,740 --> 00:10:05,500
No matter how you look at it, a middle school girl asking her brother to go buy an eroge is totally—

162
00:10:07,580 --> 00:10:09,500
...possible, actually...

163
00:10:10,380 --> 00:10:12,290
Why did you suddenly accept it?

164
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:19,260
This world is full of things that defy all common sense.

165
00:10:19,890 --> 00:10:21,890
I'm sorry I doubted you.

166
00:10:21,890 --> 00:10:23,970
As long as you understand...

167
00:10:24,680 --> 00:10:27,430
Your sister plays homo games?

168
00:10:27,430 --> 00:10:30,520
My sister is what they call a fujoshi.

169
00:10:30,520 --> 00:10:35,070
Not "fu" as in "wife", but as in "rotten".

170
00:10:35,070 --> 00:10:41,870
She can't help but shriek in joy when she fantasizes about men in love or in intimate relations.

171
00:10:43,030 --> 00:10:48,080
She's all like, "I like homos! I like them a lot! I love them!"

172
00:10:53,420 --> 00:10:55,630
Why are they clapping at us?

173
00:10:55,630 --> 00:10:57,010
Hell if I know.

174
00:10:57,010 --> 00:11:00,930
Whatever, I got it. Don't mind me and get into that line.

175
00:11:00,930 --> 00:11:02,260
Alright. See ya.

176
00:11:04,810 --> 00:11:08,730
Thank you for waiting! Time for the midnight release!

177
00:11:08,730 --> 00:11:12,560
Please follow directions from the staff for your purchase!

178
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:16,280
Now then, first ten people in line!

179
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:17,530
Pantsu here!

180
00:11:17,530 --> 00:11:19,320
Onii-chan no Pantsu here too!

181
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:22,360
The register is over here!

182
00:11:24,660 --> 00:11:27,330
I hope I make the last train...

183
00:11:42,130 --> 00:11:43,390
Did you get it?

184
00:11:43,390 --> 00:11:45,720
How big is your head?

185
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:51,390
I told you I would make you a pair of nekomimi, didn't I?

186
00:11:51,390 --> 00:11:55,060
So hurry up and tell me how big your fat, round head is.

187
00:11:55,060 --> 00:11:56,940
What, it's you?

188
00:11:56,940 --> 00:11:58,820
Can't you just mail me about that stuff?

189
00:11:58,820 --> 00:12:04,700
The server is down tonight for maintenance, so I thought I would leave a message.

190
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:10,000
I could have asked tomorrow, but I figured I might as well ask tonight.

191
00:12:10,370 --> 00:12:12,580
Nice to see you up this late.

192
00:12:13,370 --> 00:12:15,830
So, who did you think I was?

193
00:12:21,630 --> 00:12:22,970
How cruel.

194
00:12:23,550 --> 00:12:27,430
It's incredible that Nii-san has enough patience to put up with your insolence.

195
00:12:27,430 --> 00:12:28,560
Shut up.

196
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:31,430
And can you stop calling him that?

197
00:12:31,430 --> 00:12:32,480
Nii-san?

198
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:34,270
Frankly, it's gross.

199
00:12:34,270 --> 00:12:38,110
And he goes all dere when you say it. It's just gross.

200
00:12:38,110 --> 00:12:40,360
I don't see that happening.

201
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:41,610
Well, no matter.

202
00:12:41,610 --> 00:12:43,530
I'll be calling him something different soon enough.

203
00:12:55,140 --> 00:12:56,060
Kyousuke

204
00:12:59,130 --> 00:13:01,300
Hey! Where are you?!

205
00:13:01,300 --> 00:13:02,130
Look out your window.

206
00:13:30,450 --> 00:13:31,910
Here.

207
00:13:34,790 --> 00:13:36,420
Thanks.

208
00:13:37,420 --> 00:13:38,290
Sure...

209
00:13:40,090 --> 00:13:42,750
Guess I'll go to sleep.

210
00:13:42,750 --> 00:13:45,590
I should get at least some today.

211
00:13:45,590 --> 00:13:47,840
Don't be late to school.

212
00:13:47,840 --> 00:13:49,550
W-Wait!

213
00:13:50,180 --> 00:13:53,350
Want to play together? It's been a while since we did.

214
00:13:55,140 --> 00:13:56,940
Hey, get off me.

215
00:13:56,940 --> 00:14:00,810
I can't help it. I can't see the screen if I don't.

216
00:14:02,610 --> 00:14:04,570
Oh, it's installed!

217
00:14:04,570 --> 00:14:08,450
I'd Never Steal Something Like Onii-chan's Pantsu!!

218
00:14:08,450 --> 00:14:14,370
This game only has one heroine, but it has a lot of routes for her.

219
00:14:14,370 --> 00:14:20,210
Each time you clear a route, you get more choices and the ending changes, well, just like most other games.

220
00:14:20,210 --> 00:14:27,130
And there are minigames spread through, and based on the items you get in them, different flags get raised.

221
00:14:31,220 --> 00:14:33,180
What's with this ending...

222
00:14:33,180 --> 00:14:35,220
It's way too sad!

223
00:14:35,220 --> 00:14:36,520
You think?

224
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:39,690
It's not like they're separated by the grave or anything.

225
00:14:39,690 --> 00:14:40,850
They can always talk on the phone.

226
00:14:40,850 --> 00:14:42,900
Stupid! You're so stupid!

227
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:44,110
Don't you get anything?

228
00:14:44,110 --> 00:14:46,570
It's lonely not being able to see each other!

229
00:14:46,570 --> 00:14:48,490
Try putting yourself in their shoes!

230
00:14:49,950 --> 00:14:51,990
I guess...

231
00:14:51,990 --> 00:14:55,160
If you think about it that way, this is a lonely ending.

232
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:56,120
I got it.

233
00:14:57,700 --> 00:14:59,500
As long as you get it.

234
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:02,500
Oh, I need to get the other branch.

235
00:15:03,750 --> 00:15:04,500
Let Fana go

236
00:15:03,750 --> 00:15:04,500
Stop Fana

237
00:15:05,670 --> 00:15:08,130
Well, that's the end. I can go, right?

238
00:15:08,880 --> 00:15:11,090
W-Wait a second!

239
00:15:11,090 --> 00:15:12,260
What now?

240
00:15:13,760 --> 00:15:15,640
Life counseling!

241
00:15:15,640 --> 00:15:18,930
Wha—you said that this was the end of your life counseling!

242
00:15:18,930 --> 00:15:21,140
I bought your eroge for you!

243
00:15:21,140 --> 00:15:23,860
But it's not over yet...

244
00:15:26,820 --> 00:15:28,650
Fine, what is it? Let's hear it.

245
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:40,620
Is it growing?

246
00:15:40,620 --> 00:15:44,840
Yeah, well, it's been nine months since then.

247
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:47,170
Remember what happened that time?

248
00:15:47,170 --> 00:15:48,460
Well, sure.

249
00:15:52,930 --> 00:15:58,220
Actually, there was something embarrassing that I couldn't show you that time.

250
00:15:59,180 --> 00:16:05,810
You kept it a secret, and you didn't make fun of me, and you helped me out a lot, so...

251
00:16:06,650 --> 00:16:07,690
Wait a second...

252
00:16:07,690 --> 00:16:11,570
She has something even crazier than anime and eroge?

253
00:16:12,530 --> 00:16:15,820
It's embarrassing... but I'll let you see.

254
00:16:15,820 --> 00:16:17,830
I don't want to!

255
00:16:33,130 --> 00:16:35,300
It's more normal than I thought it would be,

256
00:16:35,300 --> 00:16:38,100
but there's no way anything my sister owns is normal.

257
00:16:38,100 --> 00:16:41,390
Especially that. That album looks bad!

258
00:16:41,390 --> 00:16:43,850
I don't want to know what's in it!

259
00:16:43,850 --> 00:16:44,310
And so...

260
00:16:45,020 --> 00:16:47,020
This album...

261
00:16:48,650 --> 00:16:49,610
Take a look?

262
00:16:49,610 --> 00:16:49,690
Look

